---

<BaseLayout title="About â€” Tech & Trek" description="Meet Cheng, a GNSS systems engineer and iOS developer.">
  <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-5xl space-y-8">

    <!-- Main About Section -->
    <section class="grid gap-10 rounded-3xl border border-white/5 bg-[#060f1f]/70 p-8 shadow-[0_20px_60px_rgba(4,14,32,0.55)] lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] lg:gap-12 lg:p-10">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Section 1: Hero / Introduction -->
        <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-accent/90">About Me</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white md:text-4xl">Hey, I'm Cheng.</h1>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-base text-muted md:text-lg">
          <p>
            I'm Cheng â€” a GNSS systems engineer by day and an iOS app developer by night.
          </p>
          <p>
            I spend my working hours making satellite navigation systems more accurate and reliable for autonomous vehicles, precision agriculture, and robotics. Outside of work, I'm usually building something â€” whether that's an iOS app, a Python data tool, or a weekend prototype that scratches an itch.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm the kind of person who reads chip datasheets for fun, keeps a running list of app ideas, and treats every new SDK release as an excuse to build something. I believe the best way to understand technology is to ship things with it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Photo Gallery -->
      <div class="grid gap-4 mt-20 lg:mt-28">
        {gallery.map((photo) => (
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] w-full overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#050d1f]/60">
            <img src={photo.src} alt={photo.alt} loading="lazy" class="h-full w-full object-cover" />
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: What I Do -->
    <section class="rounded-3xl border border-white/5 bg-[#060f1f]/70 p-8 shadow-[0_20px_60px_rgba(4,14,32,0.55)] lg:p-10">
      <h2 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-white md:text-2xl">What I Do</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-base text-muted md:text-lg">
        <p>
          <span class="font-medium text-white">Currently:</span> GNSS Field Application Engineer at Quectel, supporting customers across North America with GNSS receiver integration, RF debugging, and positioning performance optimization.
        </p>
        <p>
          <span class="font-medium text-white">Previously:</span> Before Quectel, I spent four years at NovAtel (Hexagon) as a Product Engineer, working across two sides of the same coin. On the technology side, I was deeply involved in product feature development â€” evaluating receiver performance, identifying firmware-level issues, and feeding results back to engineering to shape what shipped next. On the market side, I ran competitive benchmarking against every major GNSS manufacturer in the industry, turning raw performance data into positioning strategies that informed product roadmap and go-to-market decisions.
        </p>
        <p>
          <span class="font-medium text-white">Education:</span> M.Sc. in Geomatics Engineering from the University of Calgary (4.0 GPA), where I researched visual-inertial odometry for autonomous vehicles in winter conditions. Published at ION GNSS+ 2020.
        </p>
        <p>
          My technical sweet spot is the intersection of RF systems, satellite navigation, and software â€” I write Python tools to collect and analyze GNSS data, review RF front-end schematics for customers, and occasionally dig into C++ when a firmware bug demands it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: What I Build -->
    <section class="rounded-3xl border border-white/5 bg-[#060f1f]/70 p-8 shadow-[0_20px_60px_rgba(4,14,32,0.55)] lg:p-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-white md:text-2xl">What I Build</h2>
      <p class="mb-8 text-base text-muted md:text-lg">
        I'm also an iOS developer. I build apps that solve problems I care about â€” from productivity tools for neurodivergent brains to LiDAR-powered hardware experiences. Here's what I'm working on:
      </p>

      <!-- App Cards Grid -->
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {apps.map((app) => (
          <a
            href={app.href}
            class="group relative flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-white/20 hover:bg-white/[0.05] hover:scale-[1.02]"
            style={`--app-color: ${app.color}; --app-color-light: ${app.colorLight};`}
          >
            <!-- App Header -->
            <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-3">
              <span
                class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-lg"
                style={`background: ${app.colorLight}; color: ${app.color};`}
              >
                ðŸ“±
              </span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">{app.name}</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-muted/80">{app.tagline}</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Description -->
            <p class="mb-4 flex-1 text-sm text-muted/90">{app.description}</p>

            <!-- Tech Stack Badges -->
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
              {app.techStack.map((tech) => (
                <span
                  class="rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium"
                  style={`background: ${app.colorLight}; color: ${app.color};`}
                >
                  {tech}
                </span>
              ))}
            </div>

            <!-- Arrow indicator -->
            <div class="absolute right-4 top-4 text-muted/50 transition-all group-hover:text-accent group-hover:translate-x-1">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Find Me Online -->
    <section class="rounded-3xl border border-white/5 bg-[#060f1f]/70 p-8 shadow-[0_20px_60px_rgba(4,14,32,0.55)] lg:p-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-white md:text-2xl">Find Me Online</h2>
      <p class="mb-6 text-base text-muted md:text-lg">
        I'm always tinkering with something. If any of this resonates â€” or if you want to talk GNSS, iOS development, or snowboard boot fitting algorithms â€” reach out.
      </p>

      <!-- Social Links -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        {socialLinks.map((link) => (
          <a
            href={link.href}
            target={link.href.startsWith("mailto") ? undefined : "_blank"}
            rel={link.href.startsWith("mailto") ? undefined : "noopener noreferrer"}
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] px-4 py-2 text-sm text-muted transition-all hover:border-accent/50 hover:bg-accent/10 hover:text-white"
          >
            <span set:html={link.icon} />
            {link.label}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
